 Whitney Houston and Bobby Brown Bobby Brown has opened up on the influence of drugs in his life and that of his late wife Whitney Houston. His decision to take responsibility comes ten years after her death. Bobby Brown revealed this in a new documentary “Biography: Bobby Brown,” which just premiered. Brown, made a series of revelations regarding their sex life and how drugs wrecked their marriage. In his revelation about intimate elements of his relationship with Houston, he said, “Me and Whitney’s sex life was pretty intense, it didn’t matter where we were. It was about a certain look, and she looked at me a certain way. It was on and poppin.” He added, “We always felt that our love was strong enough to overcome any obstacle that was put in front of us, we would still be together if it wasn’t for, you know, drugs. Drugs just got the best of us. There was something about her eyes that made me melt inside, just the way she looked at me from Day 1 until the last day we were together, it was always special.” Whitney Houston was “the love of my life,” according to Brown, who also described the late singer as “just the kindest, sweetest person that I knew.” Bobby Brown was married to Whitney Houston from 1992 till 2007. Houston passed away in 2012. She was 48 years old at the time. Brown is married to Alicia Etheredge Brown at the moment. They star in a new reality show called “Bobby Brown: Every Little Step,” together with their three children. 